        <briefdescription>
<para>Prepare BLOB Transfer Server for an incoming transfer. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Before a BLOB Transfer Server can receive a transfer, the transfer must be prepared through some application level mechanism. The BLOB Transfer Server will only accept incoming transfers with a matching BLOB ID.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>srv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>BLOB Transfer Server instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>BLOB ID to accept. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>io</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>BLOB stream to write the incoming BLOB to. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ttl</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Time to live value to use in responses to the BLOB Transfer Client. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout_base</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Extra time for the Client to respond in addition to the base 10 seconds, in 10-second increments.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 on success, or (negative) error code on failure. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
